&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;what-changed%3F&quot;&gt;What Changed? &lt;a class=&quot;direct-link&quot; href=&quot;https://kailoon.com/posts/finally-settled-with-11ty/#what-changed%3F&quot; aria-label=&quot;permalink to what-changed%3F&quot; title=&quot;Anchor link for easy sharing.&quot;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The web development landscape changed a lot in recent years. Developers moved to modern web development stack and become more specialized. There are now front-end, backend and full-stack web development stacks. I believe, front-end web development became the automatic choice for most developers with designer background.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Other than that, WordPress evolved from a simple blogging platform to a &lt;a href=&quot;https://fullsiteediting.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noreferrer&quot;&gt;full-site-editing CMS&lt;/a&gt; (soon).&lt;/p&gt;
